204
00:17:38,866 --> 00:17:40,600
We were very worried about you.

205
00:17:40,600 --> 00:17:42,566
Where have you two been? Are you okay?

206
00:17:43,100 --> 00:17:44,833
Yes, we're okay.

207
00:17:45,300 --> 00:17:46,533
Why are you all out here?

208
00:17:46,533 --> 00:17:48,733
We heard bombs all of a sudden.

209
00:17:48,733 --> 00:17:50,800
We also heard something collapsing.

210
00:17:51,366 --> 00:17:53,233
Is everyone okay?

211
00:17:53,233 --> 00:17:55,766
Yes. Fortunately,
we all came to the shelter.

212
00:17:59,700 --> 00:18:01,100
- Sir.
- Yes?

213
00:18:01,100 --> 00:18:02,400
May I see you for a second?

214
00:18:03,833 --> 00:18:04,966
Sure.

215
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:11,033
A wild boar seems to have stepped
on a land mine.

216
00:18:11,900 --> 00:18:15,300
It's the middle of winter,
and a wild boar was roaming for food.

217
00:18:15,300 --> 00:18:20,333
It stepped on a land mine
from the Korean War and the explosion...

218
00:18:20,333 --> 00:18:22,600
scared the village.

219
00:18:22,600 --> 00:18:26,733
And skeletons were found
where the land mine exploded.

220
00:18:27,766 --> 00:18:32,633
The news became huge
in the Korean Peninsula.

221
00:18:34,633 --> 00:18:37,933
A wild boar came close to Peace Village
to find food to survive for winter...

222
00:18:37,933 --> 00:18:39,700
and stepped on an unfounded land mine.

223
00:18:39,700 --> 00:18:42,900
This led to the discovery of the remains
of people who died during the Korean War.

224
00:18:43,333 --> 00:18:45,833
The military forensic unit is at the site,

225
00:18:45,833 --> 00:18:47,566
examining the skeletons.

226
00:18:47,900 --> 00:18:50,400
The skeletons found in the mountain
near Peace Village will be...

227
00:18:50,400 --> 00:18:52,733
organized by the Korean army,
and the extracted DNA will be...

228
00:18:52,733 --> 00:18:54,866
used to track the descendants.

229
00:18:54,866 --> 00:18:56,933
According to military personnel,

230
00:18:56,933 --> 00:18:58,966
battles broke out in the area
during the Korean War,

231
00:18:58,966 --> 00:19:02,100
and it is estimated
that many have died there.

232
00:19:03,166 --> 00:19:05,366
The Korean government registered
the families of the Korean War veterans.

233
00:19:05,366 --> 00:19:07,166
Using the DNA database,

234
00:19:07,166 --> 00:19:09,400
the government tracked
the families of the skeletons.

235
00:19:10,066 --> 00:19:12,666
Mr. Kim went missing
at around February of 1951.

236
00:19:12,666 --> 00:19:15,433
After the armistice,
his family looked for him for 70 years...

237
00:19:15,433 --> 00:19:17,266
but was unable to do so.

238
00:19:17,700 --> 00:19:20,566
But about 70 years after leaving home,

239
00:19:20,566 --> 00:19:22,766
Mr. Kim came back to his family.

240
00:19:22,766 --> 00:19:24,033
His family said...

241
00:19:24,033 --> 00:19:27,466
they are so happy to have found
their grandfather's remains,

242
00:19:27,466 --> 00:19:30,400
expressing gratitude to Goseong-gun
and to the relevant agencies.

243
00:19:34,133 --> 00:19:35,600
After 70 years...

244
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:38,466
Imagine how the family felt
when they found the skeletons...

245
00:19:39,300 --> 00:19:42,700
The skeletons were secured
jointly by the South and North.

246
00:19:42,700 --> 00:19:44,866
After finding the family,

247
00:19:44,866 --> 00:19:48,333
the government delivered the remains
with due respect.

248
00:19:51,533 --> 00:19:55,000
Comrade, stop being a wet blanket
and let's go.

249
00:19:57,400 --> 00:19:58,533
Wait for me.

250
00:20:15,733 --> 00:20:18,533
So this is a Christmas party.

251
00:20:18,533 --> 00:20:21,166
- You do this every year?
- We do.

252
00:20:21,166 --> 00:20:22,566
Isn't it too often...

253
