Since Korea split into two,

269
00:21:45,433 --> 00:21:48,966
it was the first time for us
to spend a merry end of the year.

270
00:21:48,966 --> 00:21:51,966
Everyone was excited
to welcome the next year together,

271
00:21:51,966 --> 00:21:53,766
planning a joyous year.

272
00:22:03,400 --> 00:22:04,966
Look!

273
00:22:04,966 --> 00:22:06,066
It's snowing.

274
00:22:07,600 --> 00:22:09,733
It's a white Christmas.

275
00:22:10,233 --> 00:22:11,800
It's true.

276
00:22:20,700 --> 00:22:24,733
I remembered that if you spend
a white Christmas with someone you love,

277
00:22:24,733 --> 00:22:28,366
he will love you back for sure.

278
00:23:08,566 --> 00:23:10,233
(Goodbye, 2023.)

279
00:23:16,033 --> 00:23:17,700
Soon here in Jonggak,

280
00:23:17,700 --> 00:23:20,500
the bell will ring at midnight
to say goodbye to this year.

281
00:23:20,500 --> 00:23:23,100
To wrap up this year,
friends and families came running...

282
00:23:23,100 --> 00:23:26,266
with unique hopes of their own.

283
00:23:26,266 --> 00:23:27,400
To every viewer out there,

284
00:23:27,400 --> 00:23:30,500
I wish you only good spirits
in the New Year.

285
00:23:31,600 --> 00:23:32,533
Aren't you cold?

286
00:23:33,300 --> 00:23:34,600
I'm fine.

287
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:36,566
Are you cold?

288
00:23:37,466 --> 00:23:40,266
No, it's warm.

289
00:23:42,166 --> 00:23:44,500
And it's cozy.

290
00:23:48,100 --> 00:23:49,766
Time flies so fast.

291
00:23:51,033 --> 00:23:52,133
Right?

292
00:23:53,833 --> 00:23:54,666
Yes.

293
00:24:03,933 --> 00:24:07,700
- Ten, nine, eight, seven,
- Ten, nine, eight, seven,

294
00:24:07,700 --> 00:24:13,266
- six, five, four, three, two, one!
- six, five, four, three, two, one!

295
00:24:15,933 --> 00:24:17,800
It's the New Year!

296
00:24:17,800 --> 00:24:21,633
- Everyone, Happy New Year!
- Happy New Year!

297
00:24:23,515 --> 00:24:28,585
(2024)

298
00:24:44,566 --> 00:24:46,333
Look! The sun is rising!

299
00:25:05,866 --> 00:25:07,400
It's the first and last New Year...

300
00:25:08,433 --> 00:25:10,666
that we get to see together.

301
00:25:12,266 --> 00:25:14,266
This moment,

302
00:25:14,266 --> 00:25:15,600
this feeling...

303
00:25:17,000 --> 00:25:21,700
I don't think
I'll ever forget this feeling.

304
00:25:26,033 --> 00:25:28,366
(Three months later)

305
00:25:42,800 --> 00:25:43,733
What's wrong?

306
00:25:47,000 --> 00:25:49,433
People say you get attached to your home.

307
00:25:49,433 --> 00:25:51,366
Now I understand.

308
00:25:58,600 --> 00:26:00,266
Yes.

309
00:26:00,266 --> 00:26:02,800
I'll miss this home, too.

310
00:26:03,900 --> 00:26:04,966
Home...

311
00:26:06,200 --> 00:26:08,766
Home can feel comfortable.

312
00:26:08,766 --> 00:26:11,033
I now know that, thanks to you.

313
00:26:17,300 --> 00:26:18,666
Thank you...

314
00:26:21,766 --> 00:26:24,066
for being here with me.

315
00:26:27,566 --> 00:26:30,200
I remember the first time I met you.

316
00:26:32,366 --> 00:26:34,166
That kick?

317
00:26:35,400 --> 00:26:36,833
It hurt so much.

318
00:27:05,800 --> 00:27:07,166
Let's eat.

319
00:27:12,866 --> 00:27:17,333
The season that tickles your nose tip
with the cold wind has passed.

320
00:27:17,333 --> 00:27:19,766
The forsythia flowers in the yard...

321
00:27:19,766 --> 00:27:22,600
seems to be telling us that...

322
00:27:22,600 --> 00:27:24,933
our time is almost up.

323
00:27:25,766 --> 00:27:28,133
Dr. Gu, let's eat
and finish that together.

324
00:27:29,533 --> 00:27:30,666
Those are sandwiches.

325
00:27:30,666 --> 00:27:31,900
It looks good, right?

326
00:27:33,200 --> 00:27:36,100
I made it to share with you.

327
00:27:38,266 --> 00:27:39,166
Try it.

328
00:27:39,166 --> 00:27:40,533
Thank you.

329
00:28:12,400 --> 00:28:15,533
Where will you be going now, Dr. Park?

330
00:28:17,933 --> 00:28:19,700
Well, I'm not sure...

331
00:28:20,366 --> 00:28:21,066
What about you, Dr. Gu?

332
00:28:22,066 --> 00:28:23,800
I'll be going to
Kim Il Sung University Hospital.

333
00:28:23,800 --> 00:28:25,800
That's great.

334
00:28:25,800 --> 00:28:29,033
Yes, I'm glad to be
a Pyeongyang citizen, but...

335
00:28:31,000 --> 00:28:32,000
But?

336
00:28:33,300 --> 00:28:34,000
I like it here.

337
00:28:34,866 --> 00:28:37,300
I like this village so much,
but to have to leave...

338
00:28:39,366 --> 00:28:41,800
Take any medicine you need here.

339
00:28:48,433 --> 00:28:51,200
I'm sure you have medicine there,
but instead of keeping it here,

340
00:28:51,200 --> 00:28:52,900
you could bring it to where it's needed.

341
00:28:58,100 --> 00:28:59,100
Dr. Park.

342
00:29:09,666 --> 00:29:10,533
I'm sorry.

343
00:29:11,366 --> 00:29:13,000
I mean...

344
00:29:13,000 --> 00:29:15,100
I mean, I like you.

345
00:29:16,600 --> 00:29:18,700
I like you, Dr. Gu.

346
00:29:25,033 --> 00:29:28,300
My heart has been longing for you
for a long time.

347
00:29:55,533 --> 00:29:58,533
This is crazy...

348
00:29:58,533 --> 00:29:59,533
Be quiet!

349
00:30:00,033 --> 00:30:01,433
Let's pretend we didn't see it.

350
00:30:06,166 --> 00:30:11,000
While preparing to go back,
there are sparks suddenly flying.

351
00:30:12,033 --> 00:30:13,466
I feel bad.

352
00:30:14,133 --> 00:30:16,966
That's true. They'll never see each other.

353
00:30:17,833 --> 00:30:19,666
I bet their hearts are breaking, right?

354
00:30:21,666 --> 00:30:25,266
I'm sure it's inexplicable.

355
00:30:35,266 --> 00:30:37,933
Mister, slow down.

356
00:30:38,400 --> 00:30:40,066
Was it necessary to walk here?

357
00:30:42,266 --> 00:30:44,066
I have a lot of memories with you.

358
00:30:44,866 --> 00:30:46,200
I won't call you "Mister" anymore.

359
00:30:48,266 --> 00:30:52,666
I used to fall in love in a heartbeat.

360
00:30:52,666 --> 00:30:55,300
Now I know the type of person I like,

361
00:30:55,300 --> 00:30:57,033
the type of personality I like,

362
00:30:57,033 --> 00:30:59,433
and the type I prefer clearly.

363
00:31:00,333 --> 00:31:03,133
What does that have to do with me?

364
00:31:04,700 --> 00:31:07,000
What I'm saying is...

365
00:31:08,866 --> 00:31:11,366
you're my type,

366
00:31:11,366 --> 00:31:12,533
Nam Gyeong Ho.

367
00:31:16,366 --> 00:31:18,700
We're wrapping things up, too.

368
00:31:19,733 --> 00:31:21,133
Why are you confessing?

369
00:31:22,966 --> 00:31:24,033
What?

370
00:31:24,033 --> 00:31:27,300
I mean it's...

371
00:31:32,600 --> 00:31:35,700
so that you don't forget me.

372
00:31:36,966 --> 00:31:39,233
It's to see each other
after reunification.

373
00:31:40,033 --> 00:31:44,233
I want you to promise me
to wait until that day comes.

374
00:31:46,466 --> 00:31:48,300
We don't know when that will happen,

375
00:31:49,400 --> 00:31:50,966
and you want a promise?

376
00:31:54,433 --> 00:31:58,833
We could meet and marry someone else...

377
00:31:58,833 --> 00:32:00,900
and even have kids,

378
00:32:00,900 --> 00:32:01,833
but we could meet again.

379
00:32:03,800 --> 00:32:06,233
We have so many memories in this village.

380
00:32:15,866 --> 00:32:19,100
Let's go and get something to eat.

381
00:32:36,933 --> 00:32:39,400
I could tell you're not a big eater.

382
00:32:40,600 --> 00:32:41,766
What do you like?

383
00:32:43,433 --> 00:32:46,433
Have you been watching me?
I like everything.

384
00:32:49,700 --> 00:32:51,733
Then are you craving anything?

385
00:33:18,700 --> 00:33:19,433
Jun Mo.

386
00:33:24,300 --> 00:33:25,300
Are you crying?

387
00:33:33,033 --> 00:33:34,633
If we say goodbye like this,

388
00:33:36,066 --> 00:33:37,733
when will we see each other again?

389
00:33:46,600 --> 00:33:50,466
After cleaning up this area,

390
00:33:50,466 --> 00:33:54,066
won't we see each other
in about two years?

391
00:33:55,866 --> 00:33:58,066
We can't guarantee that...

392
00:34:00,100 --> 00:34:01,500
it will be us at that time.

393
00:34:02,300 --> 00:34:03,900
Who knows?

394
00:34:04,900 --> 00:34:06,933
We'll see each other again.

395
00:34:07,933 --> 00:34:09,133
Hey.

396
00:34:10,166 --> 00:34:11,566
I'll miss you so much.

397
00:34:22,166 --> 00:34:23,833
Come on now.

398
00:34:23,833 --> 00:34:27,633
The South and North spent 70 years apart.

399
00:34:27,633 --> 00:34:30,300
After spending one year together,

400
00:34:30,300 --> 00:34:34,033
we understand each other
and have built a deep bond.

401
00:35:35,400 --> 00:35:37,766
(To Dr. Gu Jin Sang
From Park Dam So)

402
00:36:53,666 --> 00:36:56,900
Will you be busy back home?

403
00:36:58,933 --> 00:37:00,233
I probably will be.

404
00:37:01,266 --> 00:37:03,300
I'll have to do all the delayed concerts.

405
00:37:05,000 --> 00:37:09,266
I'll go to your concert
if I get the chance.

406
00:37:09,266 --> 00:37:10,200
Okay.

407
00:37:12,300 --> 00:37:15,300
Will you go to Germany
right after you go back?

408
00:37:17,700 --> 00:37:21,400
After the report, I might have to.

409
00:37:24,866 --> 00:37:26,466
I don't know when,

410
00:37:28,100 --> 00:37:30,133
but we can see each other again, right?

411
00:37:35,100 --> 00:37:37,866
I can't promise you that.

412
00:37:41,966 --> 00:37:43,533
I won't change my number.

413
00:37:44,533 --> 00:37:45,700
Call me anytime.

414
00:37:48,200 --> 00:37:49,866
I don't know when I'll leave for Germany.

415
00:37:51,233 --> 00:37:54,000
Even if I knew your number,

416
00:37:54,000 --> 00:37:55,700
it'll be hard to see you again.

417
00:38:07,800 --> 00:38:09,200
What is this?

418
00:38:09,866 --> 00:38:10,900
Open it.

419
00:38:23,433 --> 00:38:24,666
It's pretty.

420
00:38:44,433 --> 00:38:47,733
On the way back home
after winning the Chopin Award,

421
00:38:48,766 --> 00:38:51,166
I bought this as a gift...

422
00:38:52,966 --> 00:38:55,400
to give to someone I would like.

423
00:39:02,700 --> 00:39:05,433
Does it look good on me?

424
00:39:07,600 --> 00:39:08,266
Yes.

425
00:39:27,166 --> 00:39:28,666
If I promise you...

426
00:39:30,400 --> 00:39:32,000
not to forget and wait,

427
00:39:33,433 --> 00:39:35,166
will you call me?

428
00:39:36,266 --> 00:39:39,200
When he said he won't forget and wait,

429
00:39:39,200 --> 00:39:42,100
I felt a rush of pain deep in my heart.

430
00:39:43,133 --> 00:39:45,766
I know I'll never see him...

431
00:39:45,766 --> 00:39:48,100
and that we can't be together like now.

432
00:39:49,833 --> 00:39:54,200
I wish time could just stop
right now like this.

433
00:40:02,733 --> 00:40:04,533
I can't believe that...

434
00:40:04,533 --> 00:40:07,833
I can't see someone
I have been seeing every day after today.

435
00:40:09,266 --> 00:40:13,533
She slowly took a place in my heart...

436
00:40:13,533 --> 00:40:17,100
and became everything to me.

437
00:40:17,100 --> 00:40:18,966
I don't want to let her go.

438
00:40:28,000 --> 00:40:30,566
(Peace Village to Seoul)

439
00:40:32,733 --> 00:40:36,966
I was happy being with you all
for the past year.

440
00:40:38,066 --> 00:40:42,833
I spent a historical moment
I can never forget with you.

441
00:40:42,833 --> 00:40:44,133
It was an honor.

442
00:40:45,700 --> 00:40:47,833
Please head back home safely.

443
00:40:51,500 --> 00:40:58,133
I'll see you again one day
healthy and well.

444
00:40:59,833 --> 00:41:00,933
Thank you.

445
00:41:03,300 --> 00:41:05,100
It was a great pleasure.

446
00:41:05,100 --> 00:41:07,533
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

447
00:41:11,633 --> 00:41:12,933
We don't see Tong Il's family.

448
00:41:15,100 --> 00:41:16,500
- I don't see them.
- Where are they?

449
00:41:16,500 --> 00:41:18,200
I don't see Dam So either.

450
00:41:19,433 --> 00:41:21,600
- Tong Il's family...
- They left...

451
00:41:21,600 --> 00:41:23,733
with Tong Il and Dr. Gu...

452
00:41:23,733 --> 00:41:25,533
for the train before you.

453
00:41:25,533 --> 00:41:29,766
And Dr. Park is sending them
to the station.

454
00:41:30,900 --> 00:41:33,433
Why would you cut me off?

455
00:41:33,433 --> 00:41:36,833
Whether you say it or not,
it's all the same.

456
00:41:36,833 --> 00:41:38,400
Also, no matter who says it,

457
00:41:38,400 --> 00:41:40,433
everyone will understand, won't they?

458
00:41:40,433 --> 00:41:46,166
(Donghae Railway Transit Office)

459
00:42:03,200 --> 00:42:04,100
Tong Il.

460
00:42:05,133 --> 00:42:07,400
Mom, Tong Il is here.

461
00:42:21,866 --> 00:42:22,966
Tong Il...

462
00:42:31,766 --> 00:42:34,566
We'll be late for the train. Let's get in.

463
00:42:34,766 --> 00:42:35,833
Let's get in.

464
00:42:51,100 --> 00:42:54,866
Now let's go to the village gate together.

465
00:42:54,866 --> 00:42:56,500
Everyone, get on the bus.

466
00:42:56,500 --> 00:42:58,466
Let's go.

467
00:43:01,366 --> 00:43:02,533
You can go this way.

468
00:43:07,333 --> 00:43:08,366
It was a pleasure.

469
00:43:10,233 --> 00:43:11,700
I'm sorry I'm late.

470
00:43:11,700 --> 00:43:13,733
It's okay, Dr. Park.
Thank you for your service.

471
00:43:14,833 --> 00:43:16,366
Did Tong Il's family board the train?

472
00:43:17,566 --> 00:43:18,133
Yes.

473
00:43:19,266 --> 00:43:21,666
Thank you. Get in.

474
00:43:46,600 --> 00:43:48,200
Woo Bin, congratulations
on being discharged.

475
00:43:49,066 --> 00:43:50,433
Come on.

476
00:43:51,366 --> 00:43:52,866
I still have one week left.

477
00:43:52,866 --> 00:43:54,666
One week is practically nothing.

478
00:43:55,100 --> 00:43:58,033
Hey, Ki Nam still has
eight years and four months.

479
00:43:58,866 --> 00:44:00,866
Why would you remind me?

480
00:44:00,866 --> 00:44:02,266
I'm sorry.

481
00:44:03,700 --> 00:44:06,066
I'm fine.

482
00:44:12,233 --> 00:44:14,066
I'm really fine.

483
00:44:14,600 --> 00:44:17,333
Come on now.

484
00:44:17,333 --> 00:44:19,266
Let's lock the empty houses and clean up.

485
00:44:19,266 --> 00:44:20,600
- Okay.
- Okay.

486
00:44:20,600 --> 00:44:21,833
Yes, sir.

487
00:44:21,833 --> 00:44:22,866
- Shall we?
- Let's go.

488
00:45:48,066 --> 00:45:49,700
Goodbye.

489
00:45:50,233 --> 00:45:51,766
Take care.

490
00:45:54,100 --> 00:45:56,100
Gyeong Ho.

491
00:45:56,100 --> 00:45:59,933
Let's meet each other here
after the two Koreas are reunified.

492
00:47:29,533 --> 00:47:32,666
I'm going to go now. Say your goodbyes.

493
00:47:33,533 --> 00:47:34,700
Mr. Piano.

494
00:47:35,333 --> 00:47:38,300
Goodbye and take care.

495
00:47:39,133 --> 00:47:40,566
You take care, too.

496
00:47:41,533 --> 00:47:43,600
Look after Na Gyeong.

497
00:47:44,866 --> 00:47:46,400
Don't worry about that.

498
00:47:47,666 --> 00:47:48,866
Goodbye.

499
00:48:01,033 --> 00:48:05,166
This is the last time I get to see him.

500
00:48:06,400 --> 00:48:09,433
The most beautiful person in the world.

501
00:48:09,433 --> 00:48:12,900
He is my man.

502
00:48:14,766 --> 00:48:18,100
She came into my dry and barren heart.

503
00:48:18,100 --> 00:48:20,333
She filled my void.

504
00:48:21,366 --> 00:48:24,100
The reality of having to say goodbye...

505
00:48:24,100 --> 00:48:25,766
makes me unbearably angry.

506
00:48:27,233 --> 00:48:30,433
I capture you in my eyes to never forget.

507
00:48:30,433 --> 00:48:33,100
This moment of capturing you
in my heart...

508
00:48:33,100 --> 00:48:35,100
is just so painful.

509
00:48:36,566 --> 00:48:38,033
Your breath.

510
00:48:39,266 --> 00:48:40,833
Your smile.

511
00:48:40,833 --> 00:48:43,366
I promise to face them again.

512
00:48:44,733 --> 00:48:46,400
Just wait.

513
00:49:21,366 --> 00:49:22,433
Joo Hyung.

514
00:49:26,400 --> 00:49:27,766
I love you.

515
00:49:29,266 --> 00:49:30,266
Goodbye.

516
00:49:59,933 --> 00:50:01,233
Na Gyeong,

517
00:50:02,200 --> 00:50:03,066
I love you.

518
00:50:05,566 --> 00:50:07,000
Let's meet again.

519
00:50:08,233 --> 00:50:09,633
I'll wait for you.

520
00:50:28,900 --> 00:50:35,833
(Peace Village to Pyeongyang)

521
00:51:48,666 --> 00:51:50,900
(Two years later in Tokyo, Japan)

522
00:51:55,153 --> 00:51:57,228
(Lim Joo Hyung Piano Recital)

523
00:53:59,800 --> 00:54:03,133
Your room this time is Room 9005.

524
00:54:03,133 --> 00:54:06,100
Here is your passport and card key.

525
00:54:06,100 --> 00:54:07,300
Thank you.

526
00:54:07,300 --> 00:54:09,000
I hope your stay is comfortable.

527
00:54:09,000 --> 00:54:10,566
Thank you.

528
00:54:15,566 --> 00:54:17,166
Welcome.

529
00:54:17,166 --> 00:54:18,833
I'd like to check in, please.

530
00:54:18,833 --> 00:54:21,466
Excuse me,
but what name is the booking under?

531
00:55:06,866 --> 00:55:07,900
Yes?

532
00:55:08,833 --> 00:55:11,600
The concert went well,
and I arrived safely.

533
00:55:12,933 --> 00:55:14,333
I'm in my hotel room now.

534
00:55:14,333 --> 00:55:16,233
I'm having a beer
to maintain my condition.

535
00:55:16,233 --> 00:55:20,300
Joo Hyung, your routine is important.

536
00:55:20,300 --> 00:55:22,933
You know the sponsor
of the foundation is coming, right?

537
00:55:22,933 --> 00:55:24,000
You have to do well.

538
00:55:25,166 --> 00:55:26,766
Hey.

539
00:55:26,766 --> 00:55:28,833
I always insist on
giving my best performance.

540
00:55:29,133 --> 00:55:33,000
I know. You're the best artist I know.

541
